LitCode 0.5 - Rewritten LitCode Toolchain

LitCode has been rewritten from scratch. Here the most notable changes:
1. ldump is not longer used to generate a dictionary of chunks. chunk_dict is generated every time ltangle is
   run, except when it is run in help mode. 
2. LitCode is not markup language agnostic. Literate programs are parsed for tangling and weaving with the
   help of a translation dictionary which is generated by linit.py.
3. Output of linit, ltangle and lweave can be written to multiple files. 
4. ltangle can work in `notebook` mode if no chunk-name is passed to it for expansion. In this mode, it simply
   expands the first chunk that it encounters.
5. Functionality of lweave can be extended with the help of hooks. Hooks are nothing but python scripts used
   to modify the woven lines generated by lweave. The scripts are read, save as multiline strings and executed
   using `exec()`. 
6. Much cleaner directory structure and Makefile. 
